  "caption": "Pure semantic search often retrieves noise.Vector similarity alone can bring back chunks that are lexically similar but contextually irrelevant. This dilutes your LLM's context.Add a reranking step after initial retrieval. It re-scores candidates, prioritizing true relevance for better RAG quality.Save this for your next RAG optimization.Follow @byteflowlabs for AI systems, no hype.",
